(4,	2,	1151208965,	'Minor Upgrade',	'After taking some post-launch suggestions, and working with some of you over specific bugs you experienced, I&#39;ve upgraded MFGG to Taloncrossing SMS 0.8.1.  Here&#39;s what&#39;s changed in the update:<br /><br /><u>Features:</u><br />- FEATURE: Sort by average score for games, which is displayed in the listing. See average on game&#39;s page as well.<br />- FEATURE: Ability to directly visit your submission&#39;s page, or download your submission, from the &quot;My Submissions&quot; directory.<br />- FEATURE: Option to hide thumbnails in listing.<br />- FEATURE: ACP - When admins close reports or messages to staff, the user can now be informed of the resolution.<br /><br /><u>Bugs Fixed:</u><br />- SITE: If a user&#39;s HTTP_REFERER is masked, they cannot download files.<br />- SITE: Some browsers will not properly download binary files tagged with an &#39;inline&#39; disposition.<br />- SITE: Some typo fixes<br />- SITE: Unable to view or download your own submissions when they were queued.<br />- SITE: Submissions could still be downloaded when they were queued, by going directly to the download URL.<br />- SITE: Thumbnail dimentions were sometimes missing without a proper fallback, thus causing staff icons to vanish.<br />- SKIN: Division between header and sidebar in the New MFGG Skin for IE users.<br />- SKIN: Minor problem with news update lists.<br /><br />Hopefully you&#39;ll find some of the new additions useful.  I&#39;ll be looking at a password recovery tool for the 0.8.2 release down the road.  You can continue to either send me suggestions here, or post them in the forums.',	17,	0),
(5,	2,	1151712756,	'Clickteam launches TGF2, MMF2',	'<a href=\"http://www.clickteam.com\">Clickteam</a> has launched their latest product line; The Games Factory 2, Multimedia Fusion 2, and Multimedia Fusion 2 Developer.  They&#39;re also offering generous discounts for current owners of TGF, MMF, and Jamagic - all versions.  This time, all three programs are conceptually the same, differing mainly in their extention capabilities (and price tags!).  Demos are available for download.<br /><br />Regular update hopefully coming soon.  Quality Control still has some work to do in the queue.',	8,	0),
