(13,	2,	1153019186,	'Minor Upgrade #2',	'The second round of fixes and additions have been added to the site.  This will probably be the last announced update for a while, as larger changes are made in the background offsite.  You can still make suggestions during this time.  Here&#39;s what&#39;s changed since 0.8.1.<br /><br /><u>Features:</u><br />- FEATURE: Advanced Search<br />- FEATURE: Lost Password Recovery feature. Recovery link will be mailed to email address on file. Also can recover lost usernames.<br />- FEATURE: Comment quoting via a button and inline quoting via the quote tag<br />- FEATURE: Guest sessions are tracked, and anti-abuse measures prevent scripts from boosting download counts on submissions.<br />- FEATURE: If a registered user falls into a banned IP range by accident, their account can be whitelisted to give them unrestricted access, even with a banned IP.<br />- FEATURE: IPs are logged with additional records, such as comments.<br />- FEATURE: ACP - Blacklist and whitelist <br /><br /><u>Bugs Fixed:</u><br />- SITE: Blacklist would block members, but resulted in a PHP error.<br />- SITE: BBCode is couldn&#39;t be used in the Message System.<br />- SITE: Relevance is consistant accross multiple search pages<br />- SITE: Opening files from location in Internet Explorer caused them to be corrupt.<br />- SITE: The page numbers in My Submission didn&#39;t link correctly.<br />- SITE: Dates on submission pages didn&#39;t obey timezone settings.<br />- SITE: &quot;New Messages&quot; messages would sometimes link to other user&#39;s messages, and give an error.<br />- SKIN: The classic skin was missing the comment edit icon.<br /><br />As always, please tell me if any new bugs crop up, or if something (like downloads) aren&#39;t working for you.  You can send me messages here, on the forum, on taloncrossing, wherever.  Just don&#39;t keep it to yourself or it&#39;s gaurenteed to never be looked at.<br /><br />Hopefully you&#39;ll find some use i