(40,	2,	1155515302,	'&quot;When things get too big...&quot;',	'<b>It is normal for your first digest to contain old comments.  If you recieve more than one of these extraneous digests, please send me a message.  This feature, as well as comment PMs in general, can be disabled from your preferences page.</b><br /><br />I&#39;ve finished the third minor update, TCSMS 0.8.3.  The theme of this update is handling the large ammounts of activity that I never expected.  Usability and appearence should be noticably improved in a few areas.<br /><br />Here&#39;s a rundown on the features and improvements:<br />* The pagination has been changed to a condensed format typical of most modern message boards.<br />* Only the most recent 2 version updates are displayed on a submission&#39;s page.  The rest are viewed by opening a new window.<br />* Comments are now paginated, with 40 displayed per page.  This will speed up submissions with hundreds of comments.<br />* Comment pagination contains a &quot;Last Unread&quot; link that will take you to comments made since your last visit.<br />* You can now turn off the &quot;comment received on your submission&quot; feature<br />* To help save more space in your inbox,  you can be alerted of all comments on your work recieved while offline in a single digest.  This is the default setting.<br />* Text box sizes have been increased for comments.<br />* You can now view submissions even while they&#39;re in the queue for updates.  No more &quot;you can&#39;t go there&quot; messages!<br /><br />Bug fixes:<br />* You will no longer recieve messages when you comment on your own work.<br /><br />** At least one user has complained that they&#39;ve lost a review, because they spent more than an hour writing it, and the board returned an error.  I have not been able to reproduce this on the test site.  As a precaution however, if a &quot;request did not originate&quot; error comes up when you submit anything, there will be a link to recover the data you entered.<br /><br />Hopefully no new bugs have appeared, but this hasn&#39;t received very extensive testing.  Send me a message if you encounter any.  Enjoy the updates.  As always I accept feature and improvement suggestions.',	12,	0),
