INSERT INTO `tsms_res_reviews` (`eid`, `gid`, `views`, `commentary`, `pros`, `cons`, `gameplay`, `graphics`, `sound`, `replay`, `gameplay_score`, `graphics_score`, `sound_score`, `replay_score`, `score`) VALUES
(1,	292,	990,	'*Sigh* We\'ve all played this game before, in one form or another. It is just the old \"smack enemies with hammer\" genre, which is, without a question, highly over done. However, it is certainly one of the better hammer swinging Mario games. ',	'-The storyline is told quite well.',	'-Cliched hammer based gameplay.\r\n-Level design could have been better.\r\n-Quite frustrating difficulty.\r\n-Skipping glitch when music restarts.',	'Mario\'s Mansion is another fangame based entirely around the use of a hammer.  The control is pretty good, due to the fact that you may simply hold \"ctrl\" to repeatedly swing your hammer, rather than constantly mashing your keyboard apart if you ever needed to smash something quite a few times. At first, the level design is rather bland, and the gameplay is quite boring, but that improves as you progress through the game. The boss battles are well done, and nowhere near as frustrating as those of MLTCO, thanks to a heart system that allows Mario to take more than one hit. All in all, the gameplay is average, and slightly better than most other hammer-based games. \r\n',	'Everyone knows that sprite. Yes, it is Ninja\'s hand drawn Paper Mario sprite, as seen in every other hammer-based fanmade game. It is a very offical looking fan sprite, yes, though its highly overused. As for the other graphics, they mix decently. \r\n',	'Mario sounds as always, no problem with that. HOWEVER, there is an annoying glitch caused when a MIDI starts or restarts: a few seconds of gameplay are skipped on your screen, though not in the game itself. This can cause major problems, often Mario\'s death. \r\n',	'The game can take you quite a while, due to the fact that the challenge increases a bit too much as you progress through the game. Once you beat Mario\'s Mansion, there is really no need to come back to it. This is partially because you\'ll be glad you\'re done with that pain-in-the-arse final stage, and because the game ends in a cliffhanger - you will not feel like playing MM again, but rather go right on to playing MM2. \r\n',	7,	7,	4,	1,	5),
(2,	291,	977,	'First off, I must note that even the subtitle of Mario\'s Mansion 2 contains spoilers of the first Mario\'s Mansion\'s ending, so be warned!  Mario\'s Mansion 2 picks up directly where the first left off, with similar but slightly more enjoyable gameplay.\r\n',	'There are now a few elements to make levels more interesting.  And the storyline is still well told.\r\n',	'The skipping glitch when music restarts still exists.  Levels could still use better design.  Hammer based gameplay is still old.',	'Recall the gameplay from the first Mario\'s Mansion. Well... it is the same in Mario\'s Mansion 2. BUT, don\'t be turned off by that fact, you will find some unique new elements in the second Mario\'s mansion. First of all, it seems the difficulty has been toned down a bit. That is a good choice on Fanguy\'s side, because MM2 is nowhere near as frustrating as its predicessor. However, that doesn\'t stop it from putting up a good challenge! A little bit of challenge is a good thing, and MM2 presents a good challenge minus all the frustration. However, a small amount of frustration within the game may still exist, though not to the extent of MM1. The level design is also much more appealing. The first level is especially, a compilation of Mario levels past, is enjoyable, unlike the dark, boring basement level of the first MM. Unique elements are thrown in again for good measure: For example, in the ice level, you are followed around by a flame enemy, which you will actually want to lure to an ice wall that it will melt for you. The boss battles are still unique in their own ways, and you can now actually tell how many hits they will need before their defeat. All in all, MM2 is quite a bit better than MM1, and an enjoyable yet challenging hammer swingin\' good time. \r\n ',	'A decent mix of ripped graphics, along with the custom Paper Mario Sprite you know and love (or hate, due to the fact that it has been used one too many times). Characters have some neat animations, often showing their emotions. There are some new enemies here as well, such as a ninja Shyguy. Pretty good, all in all. \r\n',	'Still the average Mario sounds, no problems there. But, it still has that cursed midi starting glitch? (See MM1 review.) That bumps the score down quite a bit. \r\n ',	'With a bit more levels than the first, and a good challenge, it may take a while to complete. But, unlike the first, you may want to go back to levels occasionally during boredom, due to their uniqueness. The game\'s ending is less of a cliffhanger than the first, HOWEVER, it will still make you want to drop playing MM2 and start playing MM3 instead. \r\n',	8,	8,	4,	3,	7),
(3,	272,	1110,	'This was an OK game. I will explain here.',	'1) It had nice sprites.\r\n2) Nice sounds.\r\n3) Very nice level layout.',	'1) Why did it have SMW backgrounds and floor if it is supposed to have the feel of SMB1/3?',	'The gameplay was OK. Kinda buggy. When you jump at the begining you can get stuck easily.',	'These were pretty good graphics. I likey like. I was confused though why you mixed SM1/3/W.',	'Great sound! Perfect noise! Good job!',	'Not very much fun after about 2 tries.',	4,	8,	10,	3,	6),
(4,	327,	798,	'Hard to say. Some good points, but also some very bad. ',	'Working koopa shell engine\r\nEndless lives',	'Sometimes stuck-inside-walls problems\r\nGeneral blocky feel',	'Good: When you stomp a koopa, the shell rebounds back and forth, killing goombas in the way. Never saw that before in a fangame. Other than that, It\'s good points are numbered.\r\n\r\nBad: The poor platform control. Yes, that\'s a normal TGF thing, but it makes it even worse that Shadow decided not to put ANY passwords or save feature. So when you get far and screw up because of TGF, it REALLY sucks.',	'Normal Mario stuff, but PIXELATED. Tall heart meter, Mario resized weird, you can feel the pixels touch your tounge.',	'Only Mario stuff. Little variety. Neutral rating.',	'Lots, but for all the wrong reasons.',	5,	6,	6,	4,	5),
(5,	288,	914,	'Jeff Silvers first Mario fangame, and a very good first game indeed. ',	'+Pretty long\r\n+Level select code for good replay value\r\n+Good sound\r\n',	'+Average graphics\r\n+Can\'t squish Goombas\r\n+TGF Built in Movement',	'Pretty good for the built in movement, I didn\'t find too much glitches, rather then the usual TGF movement bugs. Jeff did a good job with the level design (I love the castle level) and the difficulty is fine. The only bad thing is Mario cant squish the enemies, which brings the score down.',	'Uses SMW graphics. Not a bad thing though, as it fits in perfect with the atmosphere of the game. Average. \r\n',	'The music is great. Ranging from classic Mario music to NIRVANA. I love Nirvana. ^_^ \r\n\r\nAll the music fits in with the level occasion.',	'Many levels and areas for you to keep coming back to. When you beat the game, you get a code for a level select, so you will come back to the game quite often. ',	7,	6,	9,	10,	8),
(6,	328,	563,	'This is the first Mario FPS I\'ve seen. And it\'s not too bad.',	'First Mario FPS\r\n\r\nEnemies can hide behind bushes',	'Relatively simple\r\nNo replay value',	'You simply shoot Crazee Dazees. The engine is simple, and it was a neat idea to have the Crazee Dazees hide behind the bushes, posing a barrier to your aim. The only improvement I would make is if you had ammunition.',	'Your standard issue Mario graphics. And a crosshair. Plus, no blood! Cleverly, petals just fly when you make contact.',	'A Yoshi\'s Island stage music. Gunshot is a fireball sound. Hitting a flower is the \"broke your flying\" in Mario World. Clever how to make an FPS seem like Mario.',	'Here\'s where it falls. Just one level of gameplay. Once you play through the level, there\'s nothing new.',	6,	6,	7,	1,	6),
(7,	308,	1038,	'The sequal to MarioQuest,this game is a true classic. I remember when this game first came out, it was a phenomenon. And this game is still great today.',	'Over 20 levels, hilarious cutscenes, MarioKar levels are fun, and it&#39;s challenging.',	'Some resized graphics, levels sometimes get repetitive, cheap bosses.',	'Mario walks in eight directions, shooting various weapons. Sounds easy, but works well! There are also some levels where you must hit ! switches and open passages, you get to drive in a car, and the cutscenes are hilarious. The levels are diverse from each other. It seems a bit unfair, in the later levels, where objects just shoot objects in your direction. And the normal walking around can get tedious at times.',	'Resized graphics= bad. Alot of the enemies and the Mario sprite itself are resized to fit the big window, and doesn&#39;t come out to well. The Mario sprite is from Mario RPG, and the other sprites are from various games.',	'Sound from various games, and the music fits in good. Normal SMW wavs.',	'This game is one of the first games with a save game feature, so you can always come back and resume your progress. Once you beat this huge game, you can go into a portal and play any level you want.',	9,	7,	8,	10,	10),
(8,	313,	837,	'Great idea for a first game! Could use some better graphics but it was good for it\'s time!',	'Very nice level layouts, music and baddies! ',	'Gameplay is a little chopy. Controls are backwards. (Shift is Fire and Ctrl is Jump)',	'The game can be hard at times but seems to always snap in your mind after a few tries.',	'Very nice on baddies but Wario and the coins could be much better.',	'Very nice Music and Sound Effects! Seems if they were made for this game!',	'Not very much replay value here. Once you beat it the game\'s over. But now and then you forget how to pass something and want to try again.',	7,	6,	8,	5,	7),
(9,	301,	1024,	'Before I start, be aware this game is nothing like you\'ve ever experienced. Not in the way you\'re hoping either.',	'Nice Engine, Hand drawn Mario sprite',	'The sheer difficulty with various aspects makes beating the game a godsend',	'The reason you\'ll want it to end; FAST! It starts out ok, but later you will come across tedious thin platform jumping, especially in level 2. Toward the end thwomps move up and down at the perfect annoying speed. That\'s the magic word here, folks. TEDIOUS.',	'Graphics: Great. Nothing too 8-bit. Original drawn Mario, which looks very good.',	'Good stuff! The level 3 music is great. Although the battle with Bowser music in SM64 gets on one\'s nerves after trying to defeat the final stage.',	'No. Especially after you spend crazy time finishing the darn thing. Me, I wanted to accomplish something. So I eventually beat it. (After 100 some tries!) You won\'t want to play the whole thing again. Your body\'s metabolism just won\'t tolerate it.',	1,	8,	7,	1,	2),
(10,	19,	1543,	'The average person would expect tedious mayhem from the maker of Mario Pandemonium... not this time.',	'Same great engine,\r\nMusic fluency,\r\nBeatable this time',	'Scrapped, the plot',	'Definately better than SMP1. Continue points have been added, (where were they in SMP1?), Mario has HP, and the engine is just sweet!',	'Standard Mario Graphics, but somehow made to fit nicer together! If you count cutscenes into graphics, it\'s almost top notch!',	'A wide variety of music, which is needed in most fangames!',	'Nothing new after one run. It all depends on your willingness to play fangames over and over again.',	8,	9,	7,	3,	8),
(11,	292,	759,	'Mario&#39;s Mansion. We&#39;ve all heard of it before. It&#39;s one of the most popular fangames ever made. But does it deserve that title?',	'Cutscenes look good, password feature.',	'Somewhat frustrating',	'Plays alot like the other hammer based FanGames, however you cannot squish enemies. You collect hearts to gain an extra hit, and if you don&#39;t have a heart and you get hit you die. The boss battles are pretty well done also, but a little frustrating, as well as the last level. <br /><br />Still good.',	'Ninja&#39;s PM sprite with Yoshi&#39;s Island graphics looks really good together! Above average.',	'Your normal Mario music and sound, and all the level music fits.',	'Well, you can always use the passwords to go back to other levels, so that&#39;s a plus. There really is no reason playing the whole game through again, however.',	8,	9,	8,	6,	8),
(12,	163,	1272,	'A semi-original Mario fangame with MFGG member bosses.',	'Smooth Mario engine',	'Hammer Glitch',	'Good AND Bad. The engine itself is of a near-Mario likeness. But more often than not, I found myself with a big problem; Mario locked up in the hammer position as if he is sticking his hammer out in a cowardly futile yet inneffective manner of defense.(And it doesn\'t harm the enemies.) To right this, simply face the other way. But it\'s still annoying. The save feature is a great thing, because the beginning of level 3 requires split second decision making, so you will find yourself dead before you even know what hit you the first time around. Also, despite the title, I haven\'t found the stars to be mandatory yet.',	'Normal Mario graphics. But this uses a lot of fancy blur effects in the boss battles. How do they do it?',	'Sound: Wide variety of music. Always good. There\'s Final Fantasy, Zelda, and some other cool music from some other games.',	'No, unless you are one of the MFGG bosses and like to battle yourself, or are trying to get all the stars.',	6,	8,	8,	5,	7),
(13,	288,	842,	'This is, hands down, as of now, the fangame to be most like an actual Mario game than any other. It could easily be mistaken for a real Mario game.',	'Like a real Mario game',	'Can\'t jump on enemies',	'Gameplay: Closer to any Mario game than ever. Excepy for the lifebar, which you\'ll need later on. Some serious testing must have been put into this gameplay. The chains from the Bowser castles that you can climb on, the P-switches, and the first game I\'ve seen to employ the angry sun. Marvelous! \r\nThe only big bad problem: You can\'t jump on enemies. Big shame. Other than that, 8/10.',	'Nearly all from Mario games, and put in the cleanest fashion. Absolutely hard to tell if it is a fangame or not.',	'Nothing diverting from Mario and various other media.',	'Replay value: Not too much.',	8,	8,	6,	4,	8),
(14,	303,	844,	'Super Mario Storm. Tons of mini games starring well known MFGGers! ',	'Goofy hand drawn sprites, fun mini-games. ',	'Final boss seems impossible.',	'Mini game madness! This game is so much fun, doing all the MFGGers tasks. Every character has something different for you to do, and there are a couple bosses. Pure fun. ',	'Funny, goofy graphics designed for this game to give it a fun feel. Can\'t go wrong with bobbing head Mario.',	'The regular tunes and sound effects you hear in alot of games.',	'I found myself playing through this a couple times, basicly because I couldn\'t beat Bowser and wanted to try again, to get stuck in his machine. >.<',	10,	8,	7,	8,	8),
(15,	162,	89,	'SME1 is built upon, enemies ARE stompable, you should be looking forward to this.',	'Same slick engine as SME1',	'Picking up vegatables and climbing up vines',	'Just like SME1. The authentic Mario feel remains intact. The vegetables don\'t stop Mario from running, though. Usually you see Mario stall for half a second when he picks it up. Otherwise, it\'s a fabulous engine. (And for those of you who played SME1, Yes, you stomp on enemies now. Consider your pain over.',	'Nothing better or worse than ordinary Mario stuff.',	'Nothing different from the Mario-ness of sounds.',	'Depends on your will to play the same thing time and time again.',	9,	6,	6,	5,	9),
(16,	320,	883,	'Dodge the ShyGuy&#39;s has gotten bad reviews for as long as I remember, so I decided to see for myself. My thoughts:',	'None',	'No high scores list, no real point, could have been much better.',	'Well, you fly around as cape Mario collecting coins. If you get hit, you loose coins and some life. Get hit a couple times and die. Now, the problem here is you get no reward for collecting these coins. When you loose, there is no high score. There&#39;s just a screen that says &quot;You loose&quot;. There is no point to this game. The gameplay could have been alot better.',	'SMW cape sprite with yellow flying shyguys and YI coins. Simple, but gets the job done.',	'No sound. At all.',	'You won&#39;t really wanna play this again. :',	4,	6,	1,	1,	4),
(17,	308,	1013,	'This is one of the most popular games at MFGG. It has nice graphics, great sound effects and it\'s pretty long. However, the gameplay department is lagging.',	'Extremely funny cutsences\r\nNice selection of music\r\nDecent graphics\r\n',	'Extremely repetitive gameplay\r\nSome graphics are poorly resized\r\nMediocre Boss Battles',	'Unfortually,the gameplay isn\'t that good.You walk through a level shooting at enemies as they walk around the stage doing pretty much nothing. There\'s a whole lot of enemies to go around that take way too many hits,some refusing to die. Your only move is \"Shoot\", that\'s it.The boss battle are all the same.They run around the area shooting at you as you try to avoid their attacks.There really isn\'t alot of strategy going on in the battles.There are a few mind teasers in there but even so...that doesn\'t help the gameplay alot.\r\n',	'Graphics: The graphics in the game are nice.They came from games like Mario RPG, Mega man, Doom 2,etc.The problem here is that the sprites aren\'t smoothed so they look a little pixilated.\r\n\r\n\r\n',	'The sounds are great.They came from tons of games.The music almost fits the level nicely.Alot of the music came from games like Street Fighter,Mario RPG,Sonic R,etc.It brings a tear of nostagia.Nice.',	'The game is pretty long, but the game will get repetitvie after a while.Shooting things all day gets old and boring.',	4,	8,	9,	6,	6),
(18,	22,	1481,	'The biggest computer crasher. But also some great things inside that should be salvaged. \r\n',	'Mode 7, Super Mario RPG engine',	'Crash, crash, crash',	'Gameplay: \r\nGood: The engine is great. It\'s just like Mario RPG, down to the jumping with the shadow. Too bad such technology had to go to waste in this canned game. \r\n\r\nBad: 1. MISDIRECTION. To progress through the game, you need to press Z to examine things. One problem: You don\'t know this. There are no instructions in the help menu. \r\n\r\n2. GLITCHES. See graphics. \r\n\r\n3. RPG ELEMENTS. They\'re way too simple. You and the goomba start with 100 HP. You can attack (for 30 damage points upon the goomba) or you can defend. No strategy involved, since the goomba only hurts you for 10 HP, and defending is useless; skipping a turn is just as useful. After the battle ends your HP is restored for the next battle. The only way you can possibly lose is deliberately defending. Then you will see Yoshi STILL doesn\'t fail after his HP reaches zero. No challenge at all.',	'Graphics: \r\nStandard Yoshi stuff, homemade houses, but there is good use of Mode 7 in this game. Primarily in the Goomba fields, where all the fighting takes place. But there are crashes to follow the Mode 7: \r\n\r\n1. After you talk to the people in the center of the Yoshi town, the Mode 7 that brings you back to Yoshi town locks the screen scrolling. \r\n2.Sometimes it crashes after the Mode 7 returns you to Goomba Fields. \r\n3. Also, the enter key serves as a pause feature. But the mode 7 that brings you back always freezes the game. \r\n\r\nToo bad such a good technique had to fail with the bugginess',	'Normal Mario things, custom Yoshi voices, nothing too bad. However: this game is 17 MB. For a huge level design? No. Partly because of the Mode 7, but mostly because of the Yoshi\'s Island Paper Mario theme. The entire WAV FILE of the Yoshi\'s Island Paper Mario theme. Not good at all.',	'Replay: Not very much. Too buggy to go back.',	1,	5,	5,	2,	4),
(19,	292,	728,	'Why is this game the target of various judgements? I just like it. Straightforward and to the point.',	'Smooth error free engine',	'A little drab',	'Gameplay: The Ninja\'s Paper Mario engine does what it usually does. There are hearts, newly added to this version, to protect your HP if you get hurt instead of dying, making for an easier run. A perfectly simple,straightforward game.',	'Normal Mario graphics. Ninja\'s Paper Mario. Whenever there are ghosts, transparencies are used properly. Really smooth.',	'Sound: Basic Mario sounds. Nice choices of music.',	'Replay: A little higher than a normal Mario fangame, for some reason.',	8,	8,	8,	7,	8),
(21,	292,	756,	'It\'s another game using that same damn sprite, involving using the hammer. However, this game seems to be pretty overrated.',	'Music fits the level nicely, Great storyline.',	'Very frustrating and repetitive, Poor stage design, long levels with no checkpoints.',	'MM is one of the most popular games at MFGG, I can\'t see what\'s so special about it. To start the gameplay is VERY repetivie,and the gameplay isn\'t very good either.You walk through the level hitting eneimies with your hammer/fan to get to the end and fight a boss.That\'s it.Special power-ups would have nice. It\'s the same thing every god damn level. Not only is it repetive, the game\'s level design makes the game harder than it should. With all those tiny platforms means there\'s a big chance your gonna fall start from the bottom. Very repetive and annoying.',	'The Yoshi\'s Island BGs look well with the PM Mario and the BGs mix together. Hoever, the stage design needs to be fixed. Too many small platforms equals bad stage design and annoyance.',	'The music fits well with the atmosphere of the level, but boss music is repetitive and there are not alot of SFX.\r\n',	'The game has a great storyline but it repetive and frustrating gameplay really hurt the score.',	2,	5,	6,	4,	4),
(23,	330,	629,	'It\'s a simple, fun game that you can dive right into.',	'It actually has a working character selection engine',	'Made in KnP and has a 256 color mode, so is sort of dingy looking. The voice samples that are used are terribly distorted.',	' You have several different levels, all with different objectives, and you even get a puzzle level, too. Not that special, but most of the levels are probably things not tried before, such as a RPG level fighting against Sailor Moon...',	'Most of these are NES graphics, so there\'s nothing special here.',	'Again, nothing special, albeit the voice samples that are used are horribly distorted.',	'This is where the game truly begins to shine. You can pick from 10 or so characters, and they all have different classes of attack....Pretty nice. ',	5,	6,	6,	9,	7),
(25,	160,	1308,	'VERY nice original graphics, Fanguy is one of MFGG\'s most promising spriters.',	'Great original graphics, slick gameplay, nice music - even the intro is fun to watch.',	'Piranha Plants still come out of their pipes even if Mario is standing on them.',	'Extremely slick gameplay.  Even without tons of special features (and nary a power-up), this game still manages to play so well you\'ll wonder how it could\'ve been produced by an amatuer.',	'Probably the best original graphics I\'ve ever seen in a fangame.  They\'re not 16-bit, 32-bit, or cell-shaded - and I wouldn\'t want it any other way.',	'The music is good, although it doesn\'t seem to fit the level very well at all.',	'As far as single level demos go, I find myself playing this one a lot more than most others.',	9,	10,	7,	8,	9),
(26,	285,	1031,	'Plays a lot like a regular Mario game, just his boots are gone! No stomping enemies in this one.',	'Completely hand drawn graphics',	'Repetitive levels, sound',	'I like this game since it has a little more originality. In this game, you don\'t stomp your enemies, you whack them with a wrench (what every plumber should have!) Nothing too special otherwise, but it does have pipe warps. \r\n',	'This is a strong point in the game. EVERYTHING is original graphics. Everything right down to the warp pipes. The animation is pretty good. They may not be the best handmade graphics I\'ve seen, but they\'re really good for what they are. I can see a lot of work went into this portion of the game. Mario even starts to sleep when you don\'t do anything for a while. \r\n',	'This is where the game really slumps. There are no sounds and redundantly repeated songs. Although, the title song is new to me. I gave it some points for that. \r\n',	'I can\'t say you\'ll play this game over and over, but you\'ll play it a while. The main reason is you can\'t continue your game. This is a little too hard of a game to not have a password or a way to save in it.',	8,	9,	3,	6,	6),
(27,	302,	790,	'This is pretty good for a KNP quality game. But this game has a lot of bugs left and right. Even though, this game is a must-to-play.',	'-Addictive Gameplay\r\n-Handmade Graphics\r\n-Remixes\r\n-Great sounds',	'-Glitchy Engine for Mario\r\n-Pixelized sprites\r\n-Overused Hammer Bros. Theme\r\n-Short levels\r\n-Impossible to beat Boss battles\r\n-Unprotected',	'Addictive. However, when you lose all three lives, you have to start over from the beginning, and this game doesn\'t seem to have a save feature nor passwords. Passwords are only seen on certain levels or cinemas. The engine used is too glitchy and a tad slippery. The shooting jet level is fun, but the meter is pointless. And some levels are impossible to beat or too short. Finally, i loathe the boss battles.',	'There\'s sprites from almost every Mario game. There\'s some non-Mario sprites, like the jets, and some handmade ones as well. However, some sprites don\'t fit in together. The Original Mario sprite looks weird and I don\'t like the fact that most of the sprites were pixelated. If only the game was a 320 x 200 screem game.  ',	'Remixes almost everywhere in each level. There\'s not one single level that has crappy music. All remixes. But the Hammer Bros Music was overused. There\'s some cool sounds thrown in as well, and mock voices of Mario. Nice job, Doc.',	'Once you play this, it won\'t be that much fun. But if you want to tackle it again, go ahead. There might be some levels you might want to beat again.',	6,	7,	7,	6,	7),
(28,	303,	954,	'Fun game, bad graphics.  Nuff Said in the General Comments.',	'-Various types of mini-games\r\n-Long, fun, and addictive',	'-Horrible Sprites\r\n-You get stcuk in some areas\r\n-No instructions for certain games',	'So much cool mini-games. You challenge many different MFGG oldbies, each with a completely different game.',	'Ah my God. They are horrible. But bad graphics shouldn\'t fool you. ',	'Music everywhere, yes. It\'s a good thing. There\'s even sounds that fit in well with the sprites animations',	'You really need to play this again. But once you play the whole thing couple times, it will get more easier.',	10,	1,	8,	9,	7),
(29,	308,	1384,	'Mario Quest 2',	'Great graphics,nice selection of sounds,save feature\r\n',	'Cons: Worst gameplay ever,easy to make game style,bad minigames ',	'Now this is the part where everything goes down. This is just a top view button masher! You just walk and shoot,walk and shoot. I like the cutscenes but the gameplay is horrible. What is actually getting this into a number is how I enjoyed DK and saving.\r\n\r\n',	'We see a lot of graphics here. Super Mario RPG,Sonic the hedgehog 3, this is actually the best part of this game! The levels look nice as well and I enjoy how TD threw together the game.',	'Now this is what I like a lot! There are tons of sounds everywhere! There is even good music and even the perfect music for certain areas. This is the second best thing about this game. This isn\'t perfect though.\r\n',	'Although the game is huge and saves, this is pretty low since the gameplay is bad, you really don\'t want to be playing this.',	1,	7,	5,	1,	1),
(30,	282,	1272,	'Words escape me. This game is terrible and I don\'t know how it got such good reviews in the past.',	'Zelda looking engine',	'Long, hard, and annoying,\r\nThe bouncing boss concept,\r\nNot protected',	'An 8 direction movement with fireballs. Nothing too fancy. The game is littered with the bouncing ball enemies. And the bouncing ball bosses who fire projectiles. It\'s too trite to comprehend. Fangames really shouldn\'t have the bouncing boss with projectiles system. It get too old too fast.\r\nThere\'s a race segment too. That was too difficult and almost unfair to need even be included. There\'s also too many things flying around in the second-to-final boss. That had me very disoriented.',	'Mario RPG Mario clashes with oversized sprites, doesn\'t entirely mix in the best of ways.',	'Good Mario related music and SFX. But if ever I hear that \"plink\" fireball sound again...',	'Not much at all.',	2,	6,	7,	2,	3),
(31,	330,	734,	'Mmm... this is a nice watch time go by game...',	'Well, this game REALLY is fun the first time you play it... it\'s INCREDIBLY addictive. You won\'t stop until you beat it, I swear!',	'...Woah. First of all, the game is boring after a while. And the game isn\'t worth playing with all the characters because the ending is the same and you get the same cheesy rewards. Plus, one hit and you RESTART! AAAAARGH! MARIO LEFT THE CHEESE OUT ANYONE!?!?!?',	'Like I said before, it\'s good the first few plays and then it\'s boring.',	'These are pretty bad, considering what other graphics I\'ve seen. Still, I give Zorak credit for going through the work  of getting the sprites.',	'The music selections are good, but there\'s no sound otherwise. But, I rarely put sound in my games so since the music was so good...',	'Boring after a short time.',	5,	3,	8,	3,	3),
(32,	322,	974,	'Even though everybody hates this game, I still think it\'s overrated.',	'Lots of different mini-games to play.',	'They\'re all horrible, and most of them are disgustingly alike.',	'The gameplay made me cry.',	'None of the graphics seem to fit.  Also, you\'ll see so many bland, single color backgrounds your eyes will think you\'re trying to kill them.',	'Not very many sounds at all.  The music that does exist in the game is the average Mario stuff you see in fangames.',	'Sometimes I replay this to assure myself that I\'m not actually the worst fangame creator ever, but I don\'t think that counts, so...',	2,	2,	3,	1,	1),
(33,	299,	814,	'Should be regarded as a classic.',	'Nice power-ups, feels extremly like SMW.',	'Collecting coins does pretty much nothing as the game does not remember how many coins you collect after each level.  Also, the enemy collision is occasionaly off.',	'Very accurate.  It\'s only downfall is that occasionly the enemy collision is off.',	'VERY nice.  Although it uses typical fangame graphics, it presents them in such an organized and stylish way.  Looks exactly like SMW.',	'Pretty average here.  Most music seems to fit the level very well.',	'A lot of replay value here.  I find myself playing this game more than any other fangame.',	9,	8,	7,	10,	10),
(34,	283,	794,	'A great(and surprisingly low-glitch) KNP remake of Yoshi, the GB and NES puzzle game. \r\n',	'Seemingly glitch free ',	'Not very fast',	'The integrity of Yoshi is kept intact. Very intact. The pieces act as they should when they touch the right spots. Even the yoshi egg system works great. I only encountered one glitch, and I don\'t think it\'s any problem.',	'Hand drawn graphics. Not the best but the Yoshi is great. The pieces fly off in different directions when they clear too.',	'A happy little music in-game, but few SFX.',	'Definately. If you love the Yoshi game but don\'t have the original.',	9,	7,	7,	8,	8),
(35,	351,	580,	'Another basic Mario platformer with small extras.',	'Mighty thunder wrath item,\r\nStarman produces invinsibility \"sphere\"',	'Poor enemy stomp recoil,\r\nFireball fires straight',	'Clean stuff, but glitchy jump after enemy stomping. The HP might be a little much with the low population. The addition of the thunderbolt item and the starman giving off a sphere of invincibility are neat add-ons to an otherwise normal Mario game.',	'Super Mario Advance, SMW, hand drawn Mario and Luigi on the title screen, nothing you haven\'t seen.',	'SMW Yoshi\'s Island music. Also a strange guitar introducing the stage.',	'Not much at all, except if you liked the thunderbolt item. Very fun.',	7,	6,	6,	5,	7),
(36,	321,	1581,	'After playing this game, I understood why Superadammario decided to quit fangaming. I would too if I were the creator of such an abomination to all things Mario. Read on to see what I mean.',	'Makes you feel incredibly good at fangaming even if you aren\'t.',	'Too many to list.',	'If I had paid for this, I would declare highway robbery, but since I hadn\'t, I\'ll just sit back and laugh at how pitiful the gameplay is. \"Walk from one end of the stage to the other\" has never been performed so poorly in a fangame. Also, this is the worst attempt at a storyline EVER. Period. It\'s basically Paper Mario, but with little twists from Super Mario RPG.',	'Even though most of this is taken from libs, the graphics are still terrible. Most everything is pixelated and/or out of place. There are lava pits in overworlds, castles with white backdrops, and so on. Speaking of white backdrops, if the stage\'s backdrop isn\'t a single color or a pixelated rip, it\'s just plain white.',	'The best aspect of this game, because, obviously, you can\'t ruin sounds.',	'The only thing saving this from a 1 is the multiplayer. But even that is pretty bad.',	1,	2,	4,	2,	1),
(37,	28,	1330,	'A coin collecting game. Yup, that\'s pretty much it. Oh, and a couple of bosses.',	'Not too glitchy',	'Kinda drab, some levels require extreme jumping presicion to avoid spikes',	'You\'ll get the idea soon enough. Collect the coins. Too simple, yet later you need precision jumping to nail the two coins just inches above the spikes. Or trying to jump to the next platform with little room because of a ceiling.',	'Normal Mario stuff. Nothing too extraordinary.',	'The first half of the game has the same music. The second half has a different music. Just not enough songs.',	'Pretty low.',	6,	6,	6,	2,	6),
(38,	316,	742,	'Oldschool Yoshi\'s island type game made with KNP.',	'',	'',	'Nothing too speacial, you control Yoshi and eat all the fruit and exit the level. Dodge or eat the enimies. Levels are small, with no scrolling.',	'Nothing too speacial, 256 colours. Some DKC sprites and BG\'s, mixed with Yoshi\'s island graphics.',	'Music suits, it\'s Yoshi\'s island. Hardly any SFX.',	'You probally will come back to it couple of times.',	6,	5,	5,	4,	6),
(39,	283,	843,	'NICE JOB TONI! This game is certainly worth a look. It\'s like the game Yoshi, but I actually enjoyed it more. It keeps me entertained. And I think Toni can go farther with this, such as adding a story mode and multiplayer mode, etc.',	'The game rules. It\'s a nice, solid puzzler. ',	'Yeah, the game runs a bit slow for my taste. I think it could been a bit faster.',	'This is fun, I enjoyed it. It\'s really colorful and enjoyable. ',	'The graphics are nothing special, but there\'s a nice animation of exploding enemies and hatching Yoshis included... which is really nice.',	'NO SOUND!? Toni left out something that would have added a bit of extra entertainment here: music.',	'Yes, I\'d say you\'ll be playing this game a lot of the time when you\'re bored. I play it quite often when I need to think of a game idea.',	8,	7,	1,	6,	7),
(40,	317,	798,	'...Okay. This game is VERY good. It\'s unlike any other fangame I\'ve played. You select from one of 8 players and try to cream minigame challenges.',	'IT\'S GOT TONS OF MINIGAMES!',	'Well, it\'s easy and choppy as heck. You can just replay the racing game (if you\'re a large party pooper) over and over until you win. But what\'s the fun in that?',	'If you play the minigames without repeatedly doing one over, this agem will be incredible fun.',	'Not so good, especially that idiotic Wario sprite that makes me crack up.',	'Nice music selections.... I enjoyed them.',	'You\'ll play it over and over, because each character has a different ending.',	9,	3,	7,	10,	8),
(41,	305,	992,	'This game is sort of creepy.',	'It  has a Koopa shell engine that works (first of its kind)',	'Becomes near impossible in the later stages. Plus, you can only take one hit.',	'It\'s true to the classic Mario formula...',	'...These are crap. The creator seemed to leave a ugly outline around some enemies, and Mario looks like he was simply resized and had his colour made bolder.',	'Guess what. There is hardly any.\r\nAll they have is music here.',	'Once you beat the \"CASTLE\" (why would they stick a english word in the middle of a french game), you won\'t want to play it over.',	6,	3,	5,	6,	5),
(42,	284,	1021,	'Ah, originality.  Everyone loves originality. Originality is like the ripest fruit off the tree.  Originality is nice and cuddly.  Originality is almost as usefull as WD-40.  ...its too bad originality alone won\'t cut it.',	'Pencil graphics are original.  The starman level was fun.',	'Pencil graphics are not colourful.  The starman level was the only fun level.',	'Built in TGF platform movement.  Everyone these days seems to shun it.  Normally I don\'t mind it, but when it gets all buggy, I do.  The only Mario elements here are question blocks and mushrooms.  And the level design is poor, and all levels but one are no fun.  Bad level design makes Supertoad sad!  Waaaaah!!!!!!1',	'Original, very original to say the least.  Pencil graphics, you look at their sheer originality but nothing else.  Pencil graphics only go so far... Sure, they are drawn well, but where is the colour?  And how am I supposed to tell the ground from the background?',	'Average, like 99% of all other fangames.  The only notable thing here is the Bowser Tech fanfare, although that is just one that came with KNP, so meh.',	'I look foward to the day when fan game designers finaly realize what replay value exactly is.',	3,	6,	5,	2,	4),
(43,	320,	890,	'MFGG has had its share of useless games, and this is one of them.  You best not waste the 150KB of space here, you\'ll need it for something better, like... Paper Mario World?',	'...eh?',	'A completely useless game with no fun, no challenge and no point.',	'The object of the game is to reach the end of the stage (how original).  There are a bunch of Shyguys flying around in predefined paths, complete with predictable movements.  They are completely easy to avoid, and Mario can easily fly around in 8 directions.  No challenge.  No fun.',	'Lets just say that moving Mario backwards will make him face foward.  And all of the ShyGuys move in the exact same path, which looks quite half-arsed.  Average otherwise.',	'SuperNesFreak asks, \"what is sound, and where can I download it?\" (Translation: there is no sound whatsoever)',	'One level.  ...thank dog!  Additional levels would have made this game wven less enjoyable than it already was (in other words, it would be like sitting in the middle of a quiet road waiting for a car to hit you).  ',	1,	5,	1,	1,	1),
(44,	330,	816,	'This game is a testament to the masterful work that Zorak the Great did back in the day. If you can appreciate the multiple styles of gameplay, as well as the multiple amount of characters, this game is for you, otherwise the bland presentation, and so-so gameplay will steer you away.',	'The multiple levels with different styles of gameplay and the multiple characters made for an interesting idea.',	'The presentation is not very pleasing to eye, almost on the level of Paper Mario World. (Although I do realize it may be in parody to that game, but I&#39;m not sure) Sometimes decides not to work, but it&#39;s rare.',	'You take control of 10 different characters and you trek across many different stages. Without spoiling the game, usually, Samus is the character that you&#39;ll want to be using. The gameplay is actually quite interesting, looking at how old the game is. Big props to the puzzle world, despite it not being random, it&#39;s a neat idea. The &quot;Platforming&quot; World is a joke, but hey it&#39;s an early game. The &quot;Racing&quot; world has you press right, then left. The 2nd part has you press right and attempt to collect oil bins that allow you to move right faster. <br /><br />The game does tell you how to play the worlds before you get the chance to play, but what really hurts it is that when you lose, you don&#39;t just go back the the start of the game, you go back to the start of the entire application. It would be a little more acceptable if you were able to start at the first level with the character you selected. The ideas behind the different levels were quite nice, and I&#39;d like to see an improved version sometime if &quot;Zorak&quot; (wink wink) decides to do so.',	'I don&#39;t want to say this, as it&#39;s kinda cliche, but the graphic style is almost as mismatched as Paper Mario World. Many things don&#39;t match, the sprites are often smaller than they should be, and the explanation screens are mainly just Fox, a white background, and some text.<br /><br />I can&#39;t say that I&#39;m a fan of the graphics, they&#39;re just not pleasant.',	'The sound is your standard fare of vgmusic midis and the sound effects from what I assumed were at the main site at the time. <br /><br />In terms of how they were used, the proper midis were used for the respective levels, and the sounds effects were used well in the proper characters and level.<br /><br />Just Average.',	'The only reason I replayed this game was to re-write this review. After almost 7 years, I never touched the game again. That kinda tells me the replay value isn&#39;t that great.',	6,	1,	5,	1,	4),
(45,	292,	781,	'OMFG TEH GAMERPLAY IS SO 1337!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!11111111111114331423 Seriously though, let me start by saying this: Why does everyone love this game so? It is nothing special, really. All who say this game is fun are unable to describe exactly WHY it is fun. But I shall give you a detailed rundown of why is is NOT fun.\r\n',	'The cutscenes are decent.',	'Bad level design, bad collision detection, tedious difficulty, an overall repetive game.',	'When I first downloaded this game I was expecting a Luigi\'s Mansion rip-off, but nooooo. It is nothing original. Just the usual walk, jump, swing hammer and don\'t get hit. While you don\'t die in one hit here, expect a huge amount of frustratingness. The levels are long and downright poorly designed. And when you die, you have to restart them all over again. Wee. Collision detection is horrible - if your hammer touches a flame, Mario dies. The collisions are handled from the objects themselves so you can exect many ridiculous deaths. The bosses are also as repetitive as the levels. Its such a tedious, repetitive game with nothing special.',	'It uses THAT sprite. You know, the one everyone is sick of seeing? Well, the graphics aren\'t too bad here. The hearts look nice and authentic, and the mixing of level graphics isn\'t too bad.',	'Alright, the sounds and music aren\'t bad, but there is a BAD glitch. When the music restarts, several seconds of gameplay are skipped onscreen. Because of this, it only adds to the game\'s frustration and results in more screwups in game. ',	'Once you complete it you\'ll be glad it is done. \'nuff said. ',	8,	1,	2,	1,	2),
(46,	288,	957,	'An epic, eh?  Bowser has captured the princess, and Mario has to save her.  You got to love them deceptive titles.',	'Nirvana music!',	'Overly shallow gameplay, lacking in the Mario feel.  There isn\'t enough Nirvana music either.',	'If you were to remove the Mario graphics from SME, you\'d never know that it was intended to be a Mario game.  You can\'t pull off Mario\'s trademark move of stomping on enemies, there are no question blocks or anything.  Its just your average TGF platformer and nothing more.',	'The 16-bit Mario graphics fit together well.  One complaint, though - ICE CAVE.  That stage uses squished platforms from Sonic the Hedgehog combined with badly resized ice blocks with cracks which don\'t fit the rest of the sprite.  Well, aside from that horrid excuse of a level layout, the other level layouts are good.',	'That SMW level theme sure overstays its welcome in SME.  Its played several levels in a row, and it doesn\'t fit in.  Personally, I think Jeff should have stuck with the Nirvana music in the intro and stage select.',	'Well, you can access a stage select at the end of the game where you can also adjust your lives.  But, would you care?  I suppose if you enjoyed those levels, but personally I found them to be mediocre.',	5,	7,	4,	4,	5),
(47,	351,	544,	'A decent game. Engine is quite good but nothing special. Good for a few minutes of boringness',	'Much less frustrating than previous games from author.',	'Power-ups take out each others.',	'As I said, a quite good engine. Some things could be improved. Still it feels great.',	'Super Mario world graphics, and a little of YI. Looking as they always has.',	'Music sounds great woth the levels and most actions have a sound fitting for it.',	'Just one stage, Not much of replay value here, Though you might want to try it out again.',	6,	6,	8,	1,	6),
(48,	326,	663,	'This is one worst fangame experiences I\'ve ever played. Bar none.',	'High score list',	'Lives system is like HP, room to glitches, just about the entire thing',	'I could go on about this... the gameplay is strikingly awful. The lives system works like HP with one life, leaving room to glitches on a spike reducing all your HP at once. The jumping is kind of sparatic. There\'s passwords too, but they don\'t help much. Soon you will reach the race with \"coopa the quick\". This is the single most agrrivating task in all of fangaming. You must reach the end of the stage before the path movement koopa does. Jumping boards propell you forward. The joints on the path movement cycle speeds. Sometimes he\'ll move fast, sometimes slow. But almost always he will pull ahead of you, and you will likely lose. After you beat him, there is a part of the game which apparently stops in the middle, like the level was stopped working on. I still don\'t know if the level was indeed stopped deliberately.',	'Normal Mario things, but some standard TGF objects. Also the overworld map is poorly done.',	'Nothing too different from Mario.',	'Pretty much none.',	1,	5,	7,	1,	2),
(49,	289,	1335,	'A great game to play with high replay value! Worth playing.',	'Level Select. Saveing points. ',	'A bit shorter than I expected.',	'It used the Yoshi Eating How-to.\r\nWhich Brings up the score. Then there\'s the Portal on the tall and skiny levels.\r\nJust in case you missed an enemy. But I keep having the feeling somethings missing.',	'Graphics straight from the computer!\r\nWhich are easy to get. But they have such high qaulity!',	'Custom Sounds of Yoshi from Yoshiman.\r\nThat\'s good but can be annoying sometimes.\r\n',	'A definate 10! The bosses at the end are amusing. And you get a level select when you beat it. And with the Saving Feature. You don\'t need to remember passwords!',	9,	10,	9,	10,	9),
(50,	160,	1265,	'A great platformer, even though it is made in TGF.',	'This is the greatest Platformer ever made. No one can make a better one.\r\n',	'Quite big for a demo.',	'The Static is Almost perfect, the enimies are just as stupid as they are n real nintendo games.',	'Fanguy + Handmade Grahpics= The Best Original Mario Sprite Ever.',	'We\'ve all heard these sounds before.',	'Demos have no replay, unless you are anticipating the game.',	7,	10,	4,	4,	6),
(51,	282,	873,	'This a another Thunder Dragon Classic!',	'Fun and tricky maze-like levels! You change weapons though-out the game!',	'Mario\'s walking animation is crap. That\'s what bugs me the most.',	'Awsome controls except the fact if you have a keyboard you have to change the settings. But other then that the Gameplay is great.',	'Pretty good graphics but again Mario is crap. Nice objects off to the side of the levels.',	'Very nice sound but could be better. Also it really doesn\'t have much sound except the music.',	'Same with Wario\'s Revenge not much replay value here. Gets boring after you beat it.',	9,	5,	4,	3,	8),
(52,	286,	859,	'OMG! ....This is amazing. It\'s the best fangame about sports I\'ve ever seen. It\'s so well-programmed. The characters dribble and shoot the ball realistically and it bounces amazingly. All in all, the programming is simply put, great.',	'Well, the music rules, the gameplay rules, the movement rules, the controls rule... did I miss anything?',	'... I guess I can say there should have been more features. There could have been awesome b-ball tricks. Also, with his amazing skills he could have made a one player mode!',	'...THE BEST gameplay I\'ve seen in my sports fangaming life. I especially like how realistically the ball moves.',	'Oh, they\'re nothing special; but graphics aren\'t the main thing in this game.',	'The music is EXCELLENT, especially the one for the middle court.',	'YEAH, DUH you\'ll be playing this again, it\'s so dang fun!!! ',	10,	6,	9,	10,	9),
(759,	1971,	720,	'Not a bad fangame, but it isn&#39;t great either. It has some potential however.',	'Online score board',	'Confusing controls',	'The gameplay&#39;s concept is interesting. You&#39;re basically a Magikoopa named Rebel and you&#39;re in a field and you have to use your magic that has 3 choices of color (Blue, Yellow and Green) and destroy enemies that are in that color. Good concept, but it wasn&#39;t executed all that great. For one, the delay time for using magic is a bit too long and the controls in the game are rather unusual and confusing, but in a while you&#39;ll get the hang of it fortunately.<br /><br />Another problem is that when you use the wrong color of your magic on an enemy, the magic deflects slowly back at you and you&#39;ll have to destroy it with the same kind of magic, unfortunately this also distracts you from defeating the enemies.',	'SMB3 backgrounds + Marvel vs Capcom special effects + Fire Emblem styled Magikoopa = Bad clashing? It&#39;s actually not a bad combination.<br /><br />But for some reason, when Rebel throws his magic, his animation shows him throwing magic to the right or left. On the bright side, the magic does head to the direction you want it to go.',	'The music is decent, no complaints here.<br /><br />The sound effects are fine too.',	'After getting the hang of the game, it isn&#39;t all that bad (I suggest going to training mode). And the online scoreboard adds some replay value to it too.',	6,	8,	7,	6,	6);
