(15,	562,	1282502990,	'I heard it was an 8.5% growth in India as opposed to our... 0.1%.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThough I always said, if Corus just built a factory that requires steel next to the god-damned Corus steel manufacturing plant they keep whining about rather than taking out stupid lones to strike rubbish deals, they\'d save all their jobs, make some new ones, get a profit and stop wasting local news time. That\'s how the industrial revolution started. And everyone always needs cutlery.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNone of this exporting/importing crap from the EU. Get us some money so then you don\'t have to whine about cuts to public spending and all will be grand once more.'),
