(25,	41,	1282585354,	'i literally yelped out loud when i saw this thing'),
(26,	41,	1282585485,	'also thank you to all glorious god, whoever decided to go through the sounds in the sounds section - i\'ve been waiting for those to be done through after my decision for a good 2 months or so now'),
(27,	7253,	1282585553,	'[quote=DJ Yoshiman]also thank you to all glorious god, whoever decided to go through the sounds in the sounds section - i\'ve been waiting for those to be done through after my decision for a good 2 months or so now[/quote]<br />\r\n<br />\r\nYou\'re welcome'),
(28,	41,	1282585573,	'also, can some one fix the submission rules to eliminate the whole \"Recorded music must be in OGG format\" since it defies the next statement saying no recorded music'),
(29,	3586,	1282586086,	'[gonzo]http://mfgg.net/unlocked.png[/gonzo]<br />\r\nsomeone go make an news post NOW'),
(30,	7253,	1282586150,	'Since I haven\'t done one before, I guess I could do it<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIs it possible to post that image in the news post?'),
(31,	562,	1282593480,	'I think we should probably just axe any \"high quality\" music that\'s submitted to MFGG. The upload limit restricts the amount you can stick in a ZIP, a lot of it is of mixed quality and may or may not loop and there\'s all sorts of legal questions to be asked with newer game music. Plus 90% of it is stolen since MFGG lacks active musicians.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMIDIs, XMs, ITs, MODs, S3Cs, SPCs, NSFs etc. - all fine. WAVs for sound effects only. No MP3s, no OGGs (because they\'re not that much better), no stupid crap like WMAs. Leave all the high quality stuff to other sites which have interfaces, webspace and bandwidth designed for it.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThat\'s what I think, anyway'),
(32,	41,	1282595145,	'OGG\'s are fine quality and space-wise.'),
(33,	2567,	1282596801,	'We should also make guidelines for commenting.'),
(34,	4315,	1282603419,	'[quote=Ultramario]We should also make guidelines for commenting.[/quote]<br />\r\n<br />\r\nI agree with this wholeheartedly. <br />\r\n'),
(35,	1844,	1282603474,	'[quote=Ultramario]We should also make guidelines for commenting.[/quote]IIRC, we talked about it years ago, but there\'s no point. People will comment however they want. We just delete bad comments (and commenters) anyway.<br />\r\n'),
(36,	4315,	1282616725,	'[quote=Tragiculous][quote=Ultramario]We should also make guidelines for commenting.[/quote]IIRC, we talked about it years ago, but there\'s no point. People will comment however they want. We just delete bad comments (and commenters) anyway.<br />\r\n[/quote]<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEh, I suppose this works too.'),
(37,	41,	1282626605,	'FYI: I had RII change the Sounds section a while ago to only need one vote for accepting or declining, due to lack of individuals even looking at that section. Though it\'s relatively easy to figure out what should be accepted or not, there\'s terms of looking at other submissions and having good knowledge of intricate details of audio quality, theft and other audio issues. Therefore, while you can go ahead and accept/decline in that area, it\'d just be a nice gesture if you could leave it for me. -grin with sunglasses-'),
(39,	3586,	1282632530,	'[quote=Tragiculous](and commenters)[/quote]ha<br />\r\n'),
(40,	562,	1282649125,	'[quote=DJ Yoshiman]OGG\'s are fine quality and space-wise.[/quote]<br />\r\nI don\'t know if they are though. They\'re still a lossy compression format, they still tend to produce music tracks in their megabytes and so you only get three our four submitted in a pack, and that won\'t be a full set.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAnd you\'ve still got issues with looping and compression rates and volume and all sorts of crap.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThere\'s also the other obvious problem which is the upload limit also applies to games. So games at MFGG can\'t really afford to have big high quality soundtracks which means there\'s not much point in hosting those soundtracks while the limit is in place.'),
(41,	2567,	1282649616,	'Honestly, we shouldn\'t accept ripped music in MP3, OGG etc. format.'),
(42,	41,	1282665499,	'I haven\'t accepted any ripped music since I was brought aboard, since I categorize it under recorded music.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nI think we should allow low-space OGGs that are remixes.'),
(43,	562,	1282672047,	'Remixes I\'m fine with, assuming its not stolen. It\'s just game rips where people attempt to rip every track and submit it in craptacular formats over 48392043 different submissions.'),
(44,	3586,	1282682832,	'game rips => http://youtube.com + http://video2mp3.net<br />\r\nwe really don\'t need them hosted here :V'),
(45,	41,	1282694571,	'So let\'s change the \"recorded music\" redundancy line to \"game rips are not allowed.\"'),
(46,	3586,	1282720525,	'    Sound files must be as high quality as possible. We will not accept poorly recorded or fuzzy sound effects that would not be useful in fangames.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n    Do not submit music that has been ripped from games. MIDI music must be your own composition and not taken from another website, even if you cannot find the original composer\'s name.'),
(47,	2567,	1282723101,	'@ Char: Endorsed'),
(48,	562,	1282748877,	'Well you can\'t really say \"no game rips\" because we accept things like SPCs.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBut \"no MP3/OGG/Whatever game rips\" will be fine.');
